						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Mahāliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>[Kulaśēkarāḷva]</p>						

						<p>This record, which is in Kannaḍa language engraved in Malayālam characters, states that the king granted the taxes realised in Śivasahabra[h]maṇavūra (Śivasa-Brahmavūra ?) to (the temple of) the god at Kōṭa for the maintanance of a hand-lamp <hi rend="italic">(kai-veḷaku).</hi> Adambhaṭṭuḍeyarasa also appears to have participated in making the grant.</p>						

						<p>The only details of the date given is that Jupiter was in Kumbha. The record is engraved in characters of about the 14th century. </p>						

						</summary>
